  "notes": [
    "All transfer applicants must meet the University of California admissions eligibility requirements and the campus’s admission selection criteria. All requirements must be completed by the end of the spring term prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility and admission to UC Santa Cruz, visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that guarantees your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require completion of specific preparatory coursework and/or a minimum GPA. For details on the specific screening requirements for this major, refer to the \" Transfer Admission Screening Policy \" below. Additional coursework listed under \"Recommended Preparation\" is not required for admission but is strongly recommended to support timely degree completion. For more information, including a list of screening majors and non-screening majors , visit the UCSC Admissions website.",
    "Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level (IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the Degree Progress Unit website .",
    "Environmental Sciences B.S. Transfer Admission Screening Policy Transfer students must complete the following courses, or their articulated equivalents, with a grade of C (2.0) or better in each course by the end of the spring term prior to transferring in the fall: One of the following options: CHEM 3A: General Chemistry AND CHEM 3B: General Chemistry AND CHEM 3BL: General Chemistry Lab AND CHEM 3C: General Chemistry AND CHEM 3CL: General Chemistry Lab CHEM 4A: Advanced General Chemistry: Molecular Structure and Reactivity AND CHEM 4AL: Advanced General Chemistry Lab AND CHEM 4B: Advanced General Chemistry: Molecular Structure and Reactivity AND CHEM 4BL: Advanced General Chemistry Lab It is strongly recommended that community college students complete all required General Chemistry coursework for their intended major at one institution prior to transfer to UC Santa Cruz. Plus these courses: MATH 11A: Calculus with Applications MATH 11B: Calculus with Applications PHYS 6A: Introductory Physics I AND PHYS 6L: Introductory Physics I Laboratory Strongly Recommended Major Preparation In addition to the required courses listed above, prospective transfer students are strongly advised to complete the courses listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below. Students who do not complete these preparatory courses before transferring will likely need additional quarters of enrollment to complete their degree. Please visit the Environmental Sciences Major website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Environmental Sciences B.S. Program Statement"
